{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 336625, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Klentir", "body": "Anyone else notice that Khadgar is the only character that had a unit pre-WC3 that hasn't been killed off or placed in a instance where people kill him?", "date": "2008-07-26T07:34:52-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not true. Danath is alive and well in Honor Hold (though you can kill him as horde if you really want to). The same thing goes for Kurdran in SMV. Alleria and Turalyon are absent from the game at the moment, and Dentarg the ogre-mage was apparently forgotten about (no major loss).", "creationdate": "2008-07-29T21:33:48-05:00", "id": 41379, "rating": 9, "commentid": 336625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "defektunge", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "According to beyond the dark portal Dentarg was killed in a 1-1 battle with Khadgar who pwn't him pretty easily.  Kind of annoying as the older games described him as one of the most powerful forces in draenor and also, he has 2 heads but in the book only has 1.", "creationdate": "2008-10-15T10:20:23-05:00", "id": 50723, "rating": 5, "commentid": 336625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "87181", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Being the apprentice of Medivh, Khadgar certainly is a powerful force as well. ;)", "creationdate": "2009-08-11T13:55:42-05:00", "id": 115391, "rating": 5, "commentid": 336625, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "236685", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That's not True... [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=16819]Danath Trollbane[/url] was a hero unit for WC2...