{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 1103878, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rinicus", "body": "Referencing from \"The Last Guardian\" by Jeff Grubb:\r\n\r\nKhadgar means \"Trust\" in old Dwarven. Medivh's name means \"Keeper of Secrets\" in High Elven.\r\n\r\nI doubt having an orc say the word \"Khadgar\" to a dwarf will have him say \"Trust\" on the dwarf's screen. Blizzard's algorithm of languages probably doesn't support it that way. Plus, it is indeed \"old dwarven\" language.", "date": "2010-08-19T16:28:09-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 1137492, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "camarouge", "body": "So, Khadgar, appointee of the Alliance of Lordaeron, sent to stop the horde forces on the other side of the Dark Portal, what exactly have you been doing since the portal's reopening, and other following major events(such as an updated invasion by both Alliance and Horde, downfall of Illidan, Kil'jaeden's visit to the Sunwell, the Lich King's invasions, and even his downfall, too...)?\r\n\r\nThis guy was a fairly important character, for a while. I remember playing AS him in Warcraft 2: Beyond the Dark Portal(this game was an expansion -- he did NOT appear in the original game. The only heroes in the original game were Lothar, Uther, Gul'Dan, Cho'Gall, and Zul'Jin). I imagine he'd be really important to Dalaran, seeing as he was one of its more prominent mages. The city has been restored and everything's up to full swing, but he's been sitting in Shattrath this whole time. That's gotta be work abandonment by now...\r\n\r\nHere's to hoping he actually has a role in the events of Cataclysm. Varian came back in Wrath and rampaged all over Northrend. Khadgar was reintroduced in BC and did... nothing.  Lame.\r\n\r\nI have read Tides of Darkness(the book), and it does a good job in characterizing Khadgar, so I have a reason to be disappointed with his usage in the actual \"World of Warcraft\".", "date": "2010-10-08T06:06:55-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 1150243, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "CMDJOHN", "body": "[quote][b][i][u]Archmage Khadgar of the Kirin Tor [/u][/i][/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][i][u]Former apprentice of Medivh. Supreme Commander[/u][/i][/b] of the Alliance Expedition that marched into the orc homeworld of Draenor. [b][i][u]Presumed deceased.* [/u][/i][/b]\r\n\r\n\r\nNever did one so selflessly delve into the dark heart of magic and warfare. We wish you well, bold wanderer. Wherever you are. \r\n\r\n\r\n- Antonidas - Archmage of Dalaran[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe Valley of Heroes monument in Stormwind.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][i][u]*Until Burning Crusade, 20 years after the events of Beyond the Dark Portal.[/u][/i][/b]", "date": "2010-10-22T10:26:56-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 1169922, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "entropicdragon", "body": "[b]Conversation with Khadgar (spoiler alert)[/b]\r\nYou can have a dialog with Khadgar in which he recounts his personal history and his first encounter with the Naaru.\r\n\r\n[quote]The naaru are wise beyond our understanding. I've learned more from A'dal in the last five months than all the years I spent in the libraries of Dalaran.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]I've heard your name spoken only in whispers, mage. Who are you?[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]I am Khadgar, former apprentice to the fallen Guardian, Medivh. I'm sure you've heard his name before.\r\n\r\nIt was I who discovered that Medivh had been possessed by the Evil One, Sargeras - and that he had opened the Dark Portal between this world and Azeroth. Though I honored my Master, I was forced to slay him and put his tortured soul at rest.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Go on, please.[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]I fought alongside Lord Anduin Lothar as we drove the Horde from our lands on Azeroth. As the heir of Medivh's legacy, I could do no less.\r\n\r\nWhen the call finally came to invade this grim world - and put an end to the orcs' evil forever - I stepped forward along with my friends Turalyon, Alleria, Danath and Kurdran.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]I see.[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]My comrades and I called ourselves the Sons of Lothar - in honor of the greatest, most selfless man we ever knew. We gave our all to defeat Ner'zhul and end his madness.\r\n\r\nAs this doomed world fell apart around is, we shattered the Dark Portal to prevent any further harm befalling our beloved Azeroth.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]What did you do then?[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]Trapped in this broken wasteland, we did our best to survive. Over time we sensed that a new evil was closing in around us from the Twisting Nether. More foul than the dark orcs - it was the Burning Legion itself that sought to take hold of this... Outland.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]What happened next?[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]While my comrades held the line against the encroaching darkness, I used my magic to reach out into the Great Dark Beyond. There, I sensed beings of immense Light - of unfathomable purity.\r\n\r\nIt was A'dal and his naaru I had found. It was nothing short of a... miracle.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]I see.[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\n[quote]<Khadgar grins to himself>\r\nI convinced A'dal and his brethren to return here with me. I believe that only their power can drive the Legion from this universe. But as you will no doubt find - their power must first live in our hearts.\r\n\r\nTo combat the darkness, we must become beacons of their eternal Light.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]There was something else I wanted to ask you.[/li]\r\n[/ul][/quote]\r\nAt this point, you return to the first screen.", "date": "2010-11-13T11:23:24-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
