{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 2380609, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zephyrangel17", "body": "Khadgar's Upgraded Servant Bug.\r\n\r\nDoes anyone know how to fix this? I log into my alt who hasn't done the new content yet, waiting to accept the quest from the Servant, but the NPC follows me around and has no quest.  Other people on my server were having the same problem. Some were saying you have to delete the old quest he gave you so you could receive the new one.  However, I have no current quests in my log.  I tried going back to my garrison awaiting to see if that would fix it, but he wouldn't even show up there.\r\nApparently, he occasionally shows up.  I went back to Orgrimmar, and there he was with no quest.\r\n\r\nThe last thing I could think to try was actually going to new Dalaran with no quest from the Servant, however, that does not seem to work either.  You need his quest to start the chain.  I hope this saves someone some time, and if you have the answer of how to fix this please leave a reply.  Thank you.", "date": "2016-09-01T14:24:18-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
