{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 2302505, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Schnoodledorfer", "body": "As of 6.2, Archmage Khadgar is [i]only[/i] at the Blasted Lands location. That is what Blizzard originally intended.\n\nWhen 6.0.3 first hit, there was a huge circus in the Blasted Lands because the servers were overloaded by too many people trying to click on Archmage Khadgar at the same time for [quest=34398] (the initial WoD breadcrumb quest). As a result of the bottleneck, Blizzard brought more servers online and created additional copies of Khadgar in Org, Stormwind and Pandaria. The additional copies were removed in 6.2, but Wowhead is still showing them.", "date": "2016-01-28T19:47:19-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-07-21T08:34:09-05:00", 1, "Schnoodledorfer"]}
