{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 2398633, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Drakkena", "body": "Coming by to post the response that I had gotten from the ticket I submitted due to this lovely fellow not leaving my Tauren Hunter alone. She has told him many a time that she is not interested in the flowers that he has to give or that 'Magic Carpet Ride' through the skies of Northrend.\n\n\"\u200bGreetings, \n\nWe\u2019ve noticed Khadgar\u2019s Upgraded Servant has been an extra special admirer lately. Despite his good manners, staying quiet and a few feet away at most times, he is currently overstaying his welcome. While we\u2019re working with our resident exorcists to gently banish him back to his original plane of existence there is a possible workaround that may resolve the issue in the meantime.\n\nIf you visit the Archivist Elysiana in the Violet Citadel in the Broken Isle version of Dalaran she'll allow you to return to complete the pre-launch quests. By doing those, that should allow Khadgar's Upgraded Servant to offer the quest you are eligible for and allow it to vanish now that it has performed it's duty.  We understand that this is less than ideal but it will allow him to continue on his journey and you on yours for the time being.\n\nWe appreciate your patience while we work the \u2018Bugs\u2019 out of this ritual. If you encounter any other in-game bugs you can report them using the following steps: \n\n- Click Help to open the Customer Support window.\n- Click Submit Bug.\n- Enter the details of the bug, making sure to follow the guidelines outlined on the submission form.\n- Click Submit.\n\nYou can also report and find other ongoing bugs on our forums:\nBug Report Forum: http://us.battle.net/wow/en/forum/1012660/\n\nThank you for your contact and we hope you continue to enjoy Legion!\u200b\u200b\u200b\"\n\nEdit: Update as of Sept. 12 2016, I JUST did this method and it WORKED! I logged out of my hunter after completing the redo and my lovely 'boyfriend' has since gone back to his little world... to cry and sulk.", "date": "2016-09-12T05:57:53-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-09-12T06:11:53-05:00", 1, "Drakkena"]}